   \code{set_only} \tab \code{FALSE} \cr
}

}

\subsection{Command output}{

\verb{$render()} produces a string of the form
\verb{drift= iterations \{iterations\} numsubs \{substitutions\} fitdiff \{max_abs_fit_diff\} ...;}
}

\subsection{Acceptance criteria}{

Suboptimal trees are accepted based on three parameters:
\itemize{
\item \verb{$max_abs_fit_diff} — maximum absolute difference in fit score.
\item \verb{$max_rel_fit_diff} — maximum relative difference in fit score.
\item \verb{$reject_factor} — controls how aggressively suboptimal trees are
rejected. Higher values make acceptance less likely.
}
}

\subsection{Disabling within ExtraSearchMethodsCommand}{

When used within \link{ExtraSearchMethodsCommand}, setting \verb{$iterations} to
\code{0} disables drifting without removing it from the configuration.
}

\subsection{Set-only mode and queue integration}{

When \verb{$set_only} is \code{TRUE}, the command configures parameters without
triggering a search. This is set automatically when used within
\link{ExtraSearchMethodsCommand}. Calling \verb{$enqueue()} adds this command to
a \link{CommandQueue} and, when \verb{$set_only} is \code{FALSE}, also enqueues a
\link{CollapseTreesCommand} and a \link{TreePlottingCommand}.
}
}
